---
import LessonLayout from '../../layouts/LessonLayout.astro';
---
<LessonLayout
  title="Robot Helper"
  track="little-explorers"
  week={11}
  phase="Phase 4: Mini Projects"
  duration="30 min"
  emoji="🤝"
  objective="Design a helpful task for Reachy to do around the house"
>
  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-explorer-700 mb-3">🎯 Learning Objective</h2>
    <p class="bg-explorer-50 border-l-4 border-explorer-400 p-4 rounded-r-xl text-gray-700">
      Your child will think about what robots are good at vs. what humans are good at, then design a mini "helper routine" for Reachy.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">📋 Activity Steps</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-explorer-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">1</span>
        <div><h3 class="font-bold">Brainstorm Jobs (10 min)</h3><p class="text-gray-600">List 5 things you do every day at home. Sort them: "Could Reachy do this?" Yes / Maybe / No. Talk about why.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-explorer-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">2</span>
        <div><h3 class="font-bold">Design the Routine (10 min)</h3><p class="text-gray-600">Pick ONE job Reachy could help with. Design the routine: what does Reachy need to do? In what order? Add it to the code.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-explorer-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">3</span>
        <div><h3 class="font-bold">Test It (10 min)</h3><p class="text-gray-600">Run the helper routine. Does it "work"? What would need to be different in real life?</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">💻 Code Snippet</h2>
    <pre is:raw class="bg-gray-900 text-green-300 rounded-xl p-5 overflow-x-auto text-sm leading-relaxed"><code># helper.py — Week 11: Little Explorers
import time

class ReachyMock:
    def do(self, action):
        print(f"🤝 Reachy: {action}")
        time.sleep(1)

try:
    from reachy_mini import ReachyMini
    robot = ReachyMini()
except Exception:
    robot = ReachyMock()

# EXAMPLE: Reachy as a morning greeter
# Change this to YOUR helper idea!
helper_job = "Morning Greeter"
print(f"🌅 Starting helper routine: {helper_job}\n")

steps = [
    "Look at the door for someone coming in",
    "Wave hello with right arm",
    "Show happy eyes",
    "Say good morning",
    "Point to where breakfast is",
]

for step in steps:
    robot.do(step)

print("\n✅ Helper routine complete!")</code></pre>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">💬 Reflection Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3">
      <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-xl p-4"><p class="font-semibold text-yellow-800">🌟 "Would you want Reachy to help with this every day?"</p></div>
      <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-xl p-4"><p class="font-semibold text-yellow-800">🌟 "What can humans do that Reachy never could?"</p></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">👪 Parent Tips</h2>
    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-xl p-5 text-gray-700">
      <p>💡 The "what can humans do that robots can't" question leads to beautiful conversations about empathy, creativity, and love. Let it go deep!</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</LessonLayout>
